5:
So it is true! There really are half
machine, half human hybrids!
8:
Gush all you want, but watch where
you're walking! You're gonna run
into someone.
18: Ahh! Y-your arm! It came off!
21:
Oh, that thing? Don't you worry, it's
not your fault. My arm's been
popping out all the time recently.
23:
Hey, bud. Needin' some repairs now,
are ya? I can hook you up.
25:
Don't come with a warranty, and the
parts aren't brand-name, but for the
price it's not bad, huh?
27: ...Yeah, I guess that should be fine.
29:
Alrighty then. It's a deal! Let's take a
look... Huh? This isn't even that bad.
I'll just pop this in here and BAM,
we're done.
35:
Hello there, little miss. Interested in
learning more about repairing?
Wait, what am I talking about?
You're a fellow practitioner, ain't ya.
38:
S-sorry! It's just, I've never seen parts
like this before, I had to take a look...
41: Heh, I don't mind. Look all you want.
47:
Yep. That's how tech works—you see
something nifty, you
reverse-engineer it and make it for
yourself. That's how I was raised, at
least.
53:
Do you think Elegia's doing okay?
She's been hanging out here for a
while now...
57:
E-Elegia?! What is going on? Why is
there a line of people waiting to see
you?
62:
Oh, hey there! These people are my
customers!
67:
Seriously? You're about to make a
small fortune here, huh.
71:
Haha! Nah, I'm actually taking
broken parts in place of payment!
It's not that lucrative, all things
considered.
74:
I'm just really happy I got to study all
this brand-new tech—and so many
new parts, too!
77:
Black market repair shops are the
BEST!
82:
A-are we really sure this is okay?
This seems to be a somewhat...
shady enterprise.
89:
Well whaddya know! Looks like all
the online buzz was right—this really
is a 24 hour one-woman operation!
92: Elegia. Are you getting enough rest?
96:
Rest? Um... You know... Here and
there?
101:
When was the last time you took a
break? And how much sleep did you
get?
106:
Well, the thing is, uh... Listen, I'm
totally able to keep going, okay? I'm
just dandy! Plenty of fuel left!
116:
Agreed. So, with that being
said—excuse me everyone! Break
time!
121:
L-let me go! I've got WORK to do,
darn it! I can't ignore tech in need of
repair!
128: Ahh, that really hits the spot!
138:
Ahh... Looks like I was running on
empty. I guess I was too caught up
in work to realize it.
143:
You've gotta take that kind of stuff
more seriously. If you collapse from
exhaustion, you won't be able to do
ANY work.
147: I mean, I get that, I really do.
150:
But how else am I supposed to
surpass my old man if I don't work
this hard?
154: Is your father a repairman as well?
158:
He's the Head Chief of Maintenance &
Repair at the Gaean Bureau of
Shipbuilding.
162:
Wow, so he's a big shot, huh. That
sounds like a pretty high-up position.
166:
Yep. But it's not just his position
that's the issue—it's how good he is.
He's an absolute master, and
everyone agrees.
169:
We had a talk when I started looking
for a job. He told me I should work
for the government. That he'd "raise
me up to be the best."
174:
Doesn't seem like your type of gig.
Personality-wise, I mean.
178:
I wanted more freedom than that.
To not be tied down by anybody. To
be able to repair what I want, when I
want.
181:
I understand where my dad is
coming from, and I'm grateful to
him. But... I refused his offer.
185:
Now I have to show him what I'm
made of! That I can become the
best mechanic there ever was! I
have to prove that I didn't make a
mistake.
193:
Whatever the case may be, you can
rely on us for support. But you must
take care of your health.
202:
OKAY! That's enough chatter for
now, time to get right back into the
swing of things!
208:
D-did we not just discuss you taking
a break?!
215:
Just need to tighten... this up...
Pass me the... spanner, won't... you?
219:
Heh. Not gonna lie, I'm digging her
energy. Not that she has much left
now.
224:
I'll go tell everyone in line that they'll
have to come back tomorrow.
228:
Look... I fixed it up... real good... didn't
I...
